 {"id":"frankenjax-8gb","title":"Remove remaining production panic surfaces in fj-egraph lowering","description":"crates/fj-egraph/src/lib.rs still has non-test panic surfaces before its test module: a shape-chain cancellation expect, an unreachable fallback in jaxpr_to_egraph, and malformed f64 symbol decoding in egraph_to_jaxpr. Replace these with structured lowering behavior or panic-free fallbacks while preserving the public optimize_jaxpr API, and add regression coverage.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-08T03:22:34.434892901Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-08T03:31:43.538399700Z","closed_at":"2026-04-08T03:31:43.538217224Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-8hep","title":"Harden dynamic_slice empty huge-shape stride handling","description":"eval_dynamic_slice computes row-major strides before returning empty outputs, so valid zero-element tensors with huge trailing dimensions can overflow debug arithmetic. Add the same empty-output short-circuit and checked offset arithmetic used by Slice.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T09:14:58.724339436Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T09:20:12.912474008Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T09:20:12.910649685Z","close_reason":"Added empty dynamic_slice fast path, checked offsets, and huge empty-shape regression coverage","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-8ku","title":"Fix BF16/F16 dtype over-promotion to match JAX lattice","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-27T17:31:17.940827798Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T17:44:32.044656613Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T17:44:32.044405017Z","close_reason":"Fixed dtype promotion to match JAX lattice: BF16+BF16→BF16 (was F32), F16+F16→F16 (was F32), half+int→half (was F32/F64), U32+F32→F32 (was F64). Tensor dtype promotion now 66/66 (was 34/66).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenjax-8nxk","title":"Hoist reduce_window window iteration setup","description":"eval_reduce_window recomputes window element count and allocates a rank-sized window index vector for every output element. Hoist invariant window_total calculation and reuse the window index buffer per output while preserving iteration order and literal semantics.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-30T22:30:52.948238109Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-30T22:32:35.367693384Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T22:32:35.365828396Z","close_reason":"Hoisted reduce_window invariant window_total and reused win_idx buffer per output element; behavior preserved by reduce_window unit/conformance tests, with hyperfine test-filter mean 126.8ms to 122.7ms.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-8p7","title":"Deduplicate shared egraph extraction for multi-output regions","description":"FEATURE_PARITY next artifact calls out multi-output jaxpr optimization expansion. optimize_supported_segment currently extracts each output independently, so multi-output algebraic regions with shared subexpressions can duplicate pure equations. Add a narrow behavior-preserving dedupe pass for extracted egraph equations and prove identical outputs with targeted tests/benchmarks.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T04:12:33.735552392Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T04:31:35.680278098Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T04:31:35.678303457Z","close_reason":"Completed shared egraph extraction dedupe and duplicate-root id-map hardening","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-8plm","title":"Concatenate overflows output axis for zero-element huge dims","description":"[HIGH] Latest Concatenate oracle coverage added normal and empty-array cases, but crates/fj-lax/src/tensor_ops.rs still computes the concatenated axis with unchecked u32 addition at line 849: tensors.iter().map(|t| t.shape.dims[axis]).sum(). Valid zero-element tensors can carry very large dimensions because Shape::element_count multiplies in u64 and any zero dimension yields element_count=0, so TensorValue::new accepts shapes like [u32::MAX, 0] with an empty element vector.\n\nRepro: create a = TensorValue::new(DType::I64, Shape { dims: vec![u32::MAX, 0] }, vec![]) and b = TensorValue::new(DType::I64, Shape { dims: vec![1, 0] }, vec![]), wrap them as Value::Tensor, set params { \"dimension\": \"0\" }, then call eval_primitive(Primitive::Concatenate, &[a, b], &params). Current debug/test builds panic when summing u32::MAX + 1; optimized builds can wrap the output axis to 0 and return the wrong shape.\n\nExpected: use checked addition for the concatenated axis and return a typed EvalError when the output axis exceeds u32::MAX; also use checked multiplication for total output element count before allocating. Add a regression test using the zero-element huge-dim repro so it does not allocate.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T07:59:33.400719541Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T08:20:06.881318056Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T08:20:06.879483253Z","close_reason":"Rejected overflowing Concatenate output axes and checked output element products","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
